$1 trillion infrastructure bill directs funding to ports to invest in cleaner equipment that would help them repair relationships with communities and pursue environmental justice.\n"}],"markDefs":[],"style":"normal"}],"_rawBody":[{"_key":"6bcb71e8ee58","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"6bcb71e8ee580","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Exasperated, Vicki Cruz prays, “God, where do you want me?”"}],"markDefs":[],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"97664608d9eb","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"97664608d9eb0","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"She loves the East End. It’s where she grew up. But she doesn’t know how much longer she can take it."}],"markDefs":[],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"02bbb95c2c93","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"02bbb95c2c930","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"She had a long year. Her asthma medication became too expensive, so she’s been going without. An essential worker, she recovered from COVID just in time for the state’s creaky power grid to fail and the winter freeze to burst pipes at the house that’s been in her family for generations."}],"markDefs":[],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"97423467e8f1","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"97423467e8f10","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Every day, she breathed air degraded, in part, by pollution blowing in from the port, developed, maintained and operated by Port Houston. There are many sources of harmful emissions along the Ship Channel, but regulation falls to an uncoordinated armada of agencies, none of which the public-private port is accountable to alone. Everyone’s looking at something, but no one’s watching everything. That lets bad things happen. In 2013, port operations and equipment were responsible for releasing "},{"_key":"97423467e8f11","_type":"span","marks":["842a6dd5773a"],"text":"at least four times more"},{"_key":"97423467e8f12","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":" of the poisonous, "},{"_key":"97423467e8f13","_type":"span","marks":["77ade8ed387c"],"text":"smog-forming nitrogen oxides"},{"_key":"97423467e8f14","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":" (NOx) than "},{"_key":"97423467e8f15","_type":"span","marks":["a5f7a7cdcff4"],"text":"Exxon Mobil’s Baytown plant"},{"_key":"97423467e8f16","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"."}],"markDefs":[{"_key":"842a6dd5773a","_type":"link","href":"https://urldefense.com/v3/__https:/nam11.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https*3A*2F*2Fporthouston.com*2Fwp-content*2Fuploads*2FCASP_Clean-Air-Strategy-Plan_2021-Update_Port-Houston_v20210122.pdf&data=04*7C01*7Cawest*40edf.org*7C00a61180cfe74bd4b7a008d96be8eb67*7Cfe4574edbcfd4bf0bde843713c3f434f*7C0*7C0*7C637659471469887116*7CUnknown*7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0*3D*7C1000&sdata=L4gZy*2BZ8hnoIsGgE*2F0Kn*2FTFuY0RLC9WrUli1Bled*2Fq8*3D&reserved=0__;JSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSU!!Ivohdkk!wBT4mWXIUjIh92btQBDJNXoPZqNTqxglXOivdCifXb8SPfidInz-OrqAkcnmiCs%24"},{"_key":"77ade8ed387c","_type":"link","href":"https://urldefense.com/v3/__https:/nam11.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https*3A*2F*2Fwww3.epa.gov*2Fregion1*2Fairquality*2Fnox.html&data=04*7C01*7Cawest*40edf.org*7C00a61180cfe74bd4b7a008d96be8eb67*7Cfe4574edbcfd4bf0bde843713c3f434f*7C0*7C0*7C637659471469897069*7CUnknown*7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0*3D*7C1000&sdata=bLNZfkR0Iw4jqfwKYTrD*2FsGYon31Avt8CTRJXRatQBg*3D&reserved=0__;JSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSU!!Ivohdkk!wBT4mWXIUjIh92btQBDJNXoPZqNTqxglXOivdCifXb8SPfidInz-OrqArJYOj5o%24"},{"_key":"a5f7a7cdcff4","_type":"link","href":"https://urldefense.com/v3/__https:/nam11.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https*3A*2F*2Fwww.epa.gov*2Fair-emissions-inventories*2Fnational-emissions-inventory-nei&data=04*7C01*7Cawest*40edf.org*7C00a61180cfe74bd4b7a008d96be8eb67*7Cfe4574edbcfd4bf0bde843713c3f434f*7C0*7C0*7C637659471469897069*7CUnknown*7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0*3D*7C1000&sdata=g9h8vNdNeHt2jmdAkXOXX2H91eF5gQpi3WCuj4OOqvE*3D&reserved=0__;JSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSUl!!Ivohdkk!wBT4mWXIUjIh92btQBDJNXoPZqNTqxglXOivdCifXb8SPfidInz-OrqAbzsGAbc%24"}],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"c0d6a8a02fd9","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"c0d6a8a02fd90","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Cruz lives in the center of it, in a historically Hispanic community that now has "},{"_key":"c0d6a8a02fd91","_type":"span","marks":["2ddebc2ceea5"],"text":"the second-highest rate of pollution exposure in the entire eight-county region"},{"_key":"c0d6a8a02fd92","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":". It’s the nitrogen oxides, soot and volatile organic compounds from the port, yes, and it’s the "},{"_key":"c0d6a8a02fd93","_type":"span","marks":["576dbcec5c38"],"text":"1,3-butadiene from chemical producers,"},{"_key":"c0d6a8a02fd94","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":" the lead and arsenic aerosols from metal recyclers, the grit from concrete crushers. It all adds up. In Manchester, a few miles from Cruz’s house, "},{"_key":"c0d6a8a02fd95","_type":"span","marks":["472b8b965f20"],"text":"cancer rates are 22 percent higher"},{"_key":"c0d6a8a02fd96","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":" than the rest of the city. During Hurricane Harvey, as petrochemical equipment failed and plants shut down, "},{"_key":"c0d6a8a02fd97","_type":"span","marks":["c3292fadf919"],"text":"nearly 94 percent of the extra toxic emissions"},{"_key":"c0d6a8a02fd98","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":" in all of Harris County were concentrated around here, almost solely in Hispanic, Black and low-wealth communities."}],"markDefs":[{"_key":"2ddebc2ceea5","_type":"link","href":"https://urldefense.com/v3/__https:/nam11.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https*3A*2F*2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov*2Fpmc*2Farticles*2FPMC7068489*2F&data=04*7C01*7Cawest*40edf.org*7C00a61180cfe74bd4b7a008d96be8eb67*7Cfe4574edbcfd4bf0bde843713c3f434f*7C0*7C0*7C637659471469926932*7CUnknown*7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0*3D*7C1000&sdata=qzLnkrVftSSZ6HtNXDKzEKWWogsAfZhroAQwzMDzTSE*3D&reserved=0__;JSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSU!!Ivohdkk!wBT4mWXIUjIh92btQBDJNXoPZqNTqxglXOivdCifXb8SPfidInz-OrqAtGhoBmY%24"},{"_key":"576dbcec5c38","_type":"link","href":"https://urldefense.com/v3/__https:/nam11.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https*3A*2F*2Fonebreathhou.org*2Fnewsroom*2F2021*2F05*2Fbutadiene-tpc-group-toxic-illegal-air-pollution-houston-texas*2F&data=04*7C01*7Cawest*40edf.org*7C00a61180cfe74bd4b7a008d96be8eb67*7Cfe4574edbcfd4bf0bde843713c3f434f*7C0*7C0*7C637659471469926932*7CUnknown*7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0*3D*7C1000&sdata=lLSsdES*2BiyFhS9d*2FT3cut7DCaI1Dw22TxPXsEM2cjDA*3D&reserved=0__;JSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSU!!Ivohdkk!wBT4mWXIUjIh92btQBDJNXoPZqNTqxglXOivdCifXb8SPfidInz-OrqA40N2gZo%24"},{"_key":"472b8b965f20","_type":"link","href":"https://urldefense.com/v3/__https:/nam11.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https*3A*2F*2Fwww.houstontx.gov*2Fhealth*2Fchs*2FHarrisburg-Manchester.pdf&data=04*7C01*7Cawest*40edf.org*7C00a61180cfe74bd4b7a008d96be8eb67*7Cfe4574edbcfd4bf0bde843713c3f434f*7C0*7C0*7C637659471469936894*7CUnknown*7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0*3D*7C1000&sdata=6UlRfB1Hs5PdpxuFRaP*2BNnlumkSHj88Q8p1BiDzBkY8*3D&reserved=0__;JSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSU!!Ivohdkk!wBT4mWXIUjIh92btQBDJNXoPZqNTqxglXOivdCifXb8SPfidInz-OrqA0QAYVWQ%24"},{"_key":"c3292fadf919","_type":"link","href":"https://urldefense.com/v3/__https:/nam11.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https*3A*2F*2Fwww.epa.gov*2Foffice-inspector-general*2Freport-epa-needs-improve-its-emergency-planning-better-address-air-quality&data=04*7C01*7Cawest*40edf.org*7C00a61180cfe74bd4b7a008d96be8eb67*7Cfe4574edbcfd4bf0bde843713c3f434f*7C0*7C0*7C637659471469946861*7CUnknown*7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0*3D*7C1000&sdata=oq33bajtUfpwb6p8IEbZX*2B70FILwaptJO5*2BUfNRnFWo*3D&reserved=0__;JSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSU!!Ivohdkk!wBT4mWXIUjIh92btQBDJNXoPZqNTqxglXOivdCifXb8SPfidInz-OrqAL87x4VE%24"}],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"34c439da7fb3","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"34c439da7fb30","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"It all seems too much sometimes, Cruz says. “It’s like, ‘Take care of yourself. Get healthy. Sell your dang house and get the hell out of the neighborhood, because all you’re doing is killing yourself.’”"}],"markDefs":[],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"9e36455f4b1e","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"9e36455f4b1e0","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Cruz shouldn’t have to leave, but the port leadership hasn’t done enough to make her feel safe enough to stay. The infrastructure bill moving through Congress presents a real opportunity to change that, though, providing money for ports to retire old, polluting equipment. The port’s nearly "},{"_key":"9e36455f4b1e1","_type":"span","marks":["e943884b54b7"],"text":"$1 billion Project 11"},{"_key":"9e36455f4b1e2","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":" to deepen and widen the Ship Channel for "},{"_key":"9e36455f4b1e3","_type":"span","marks":["afbc6e5ec726"],"text":"“economic growth,”"},{"_key":"9e36455f4b1e4","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":" for example, will use diesel-fueled dredges that will emit about four thousand tons of smog-forming pollutants during years of construction. They say the project will make the port safer and more efficient, eventually, but they haven’t said they’ll spend a single dollar to reduce the emissions while they’re doing the digging."}],"markDefs":[{"_key":"e943884b54b7","_type":"link","href":"https://urldefense.com/v3/__https:/nam11.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https*3A*2F*2Fwww.houstonchronicle.com*2Fopinion*2Foutlook*2Farticle*2FOpinion-Port-wants-to-become-an-environmental-15813852.php&data=04*7C01*7Cawest*40edf.org*7C00a61180cfe74bd4b7a008d96be8eb67*7Cfe4574edbcfd4bf0bde843713c3f434f*7C0*7C0*7C637659471469946861*7CUnknown*7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0*3D*7C1000&sdata=*2BEb7HowJ*2F1LRzIYzjs*2B8WXyql1k6yoAYkRpC8*2BPGosE*3D&reserved=0__;JSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSUl!!Ivohdkk!wBT4mWXIUjIh92btQBDJNXoPZqNTqxglXOivdCifXb8SPfidInz-OrqA80n_vgc%24"},{"_key":"afbc6e5ec726","_type":"link","href":"https://urldefense.com/v3/__https:/nam11.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https*3A*2F*2Fwww.expandthehoustonshipchannel.com*2F&data=04*7C01*7Cawest*40edf.org*7C00a61180cfe74bd4b7a008d96be8eb67*7Cfe4574edbcfd4bf0bde843713c3f434f*7C0*7C0*7C637659471469956810*7CUnknown*7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0*3D*7C1000&sdata=b1C6moIDjstL3WvbvIqpqblS8CNhP3FUw*2BAoyC83j28*3D&reserved=0__;JSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSUl!!Ivohdkk!wBT4mWXIUjIh92btQBDJNXoPZqNTqxglXOivdCifXb8SPfidInz-OrqAd9NVlAI%24"}],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"3082b9490c55","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"3082b9490c550","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Meanwhile, every summer, smog, or ground-level ozone, can make the air hurt to breathe, forcing children and anyone with asthma to stay inside to protect themselves. No one is spared. Though people who live closest in the Ship Channel communities — Magnolia Park, Manchester, Channelview, Deer Park, Galena Park, Pasadena, Pleasantville — are harmed the most, for the longest, by this pollution, it blows "},{"_key":"3082b9490c551","_type":"span","marks":["e86819bf5646"],"text":"everywhere"},{"_key":"3082b9490c552","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":", west out to the Energy Corridor and north up to Conroe. Soot, tiny particles that lodge in the lungs and enter the bloodstream, the Harvard School of Public Health and Environmental Defense Fund found, caused Houston in just one year nearly $50 billion in economic damages and "},{"_key":"3082b9490c553","_type":"span","marks":["013fc23e36b6"],"text":"more than 5,000 early deaths"},{"_key":"3082b9490c554","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"."}],"markDefs":[{"_key":"e86819bf5646","_type":"link","href":"https://urldefense.com/v3/__https:/nam11.safelink