e years. The Port of Los Angeles says they will retire all their old equipment by 2030. Port Houston hasn’t said they ever will."}],"markDefs":[{"_key":"082355c93382","_type":"link","href":"https://urldefense.com/v3/__https:/nam11.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http*3A*2F*2Fwww.trainweb.org*2Fsouthwestshorts*2Fptra.html&data=04*7C01*7Cawest*40edf.org*7C00a61180cfe74bd4b7a008d96be8eb67*7Cfe4574edbcfd4bf0bde843713c3f434f*7C0*7C0*7C637659471469966764*7CUnknown*7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0*3D*7C1000&sdata=kVovg2YPOvi8e032vnn2z3wx*2FSNbecCcXL1Gysxbqk4*3D&reserved=0__;JSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJQ!!Ivohdkk!wBT4mWXIUjIh92btQBDJNXoPZqNTqxglXOivdCifXb8SPfidInz-OrqAuQZDUCk%24"},{"_key":"adffa8cd1209","_type":"link","href":"https://urldefense.com/v3/__https:/nam11.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https*3A*2F*2Fporthouston.com*2Fwp-content*2Fuploads*2FPHA_Other_Revenues_2019.pdf&data=04*7C01*7Cawest*40edf.org*7C00a61180cfe74bd4b7a008d96be8eb67*7Cfe4574edbcfd4bf0bde843713c3f434f*7C0*7C0*7C637659471469976733*7CUnknown*7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0*3D*7C1000&sdata=0UjgNev3*2BZIqqzXAmMEbbmRKiQPOsCX8lucZxOcJEvU*3D&reserved=0__;JSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSU!!Ivohdkk!wBT4mWXIUjIh92btQBDJNXoPZqNTqxglXOivdCifXb8SPfidInz-OrqAIixWncg%24"},{"_key":"04b528389e48","_type":"link","href":"https://urldefense.com/v3/__https:/nam11.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https*3A*2F*2Fwww.hctax.net*2Fproperty*2FTaxStatement*3Faccount*3DFUD93*2Fdhbnbxyz3LaJES0FglDsRBRWbfxpCSyMu6eq8*3D&data=04*7C01*7Cawest*40edf.org*7C00a61180cfe74bd4b7a008d96be8eb67*7Cfe4574edbcfd4bf0bde843713c3f434f*7C0*7C0*7C637659471469986691*7CUnknown*7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0*3D*7C1000&sdata=8wSOSjUREDJxG5RL7nrzPsND*2BEkIwZy9ce5lUdyoQe0*3D&reserved=0__;JSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSU!!Ivohdkk!wBT4mWXIUjIh92btQBDJNXoPZqNTqxglXOivdCifXb8SPfidInz-OrqA4mRNw_8%24"}],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"c37db1ba817a","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"c37db1ba817a0","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"If the "},{"_key":"c37db1ba817a1","_type":"span","marks":["62752afe4b7e"],"text":"$1.2 trillion infrastructure bill"},{"_key":"c37db1ba817a2","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":" that has passed through the Senate makes it through the House, the port will need a new excuse for keeping the dirty equipment around. The bill would direct "},{"_key":"c37db1ba817a3","_type":"span","marks":["dfe2c06db0e0"],"text":"$17 billion"},{"_key":"c37db1ba817a4","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":" in the next five years specifically for ports to transition to zero-emissions, electric equipment and reduce overall pollution."}],"markDefs":[{"_key":"62752afe4b7e","_type":"link","href":"https://urldefense.com/v3/__https:/nam11.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https*3A*2F*2Fwww.nytimes.com*2F2021*2F08*2F10*2Fus*2Fpolitics*2Finfrastructure-bill-passes.html&data=04*7C01*7Cawest*40edf.org*7C00a61180cfe74bd4b7a008d96be8eb67*7Cfe4574edbcfd4bf0bde843713c3f434f*7C0*7C0*7C637659471469986691*7CUnknown*7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0*3D*7C1000&sdata=HYIR5DJib3RCHGrjW510OKn*2F1QfvJcL4fTYI2OKYpZs*3D&reserved=0__;JSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSU!!Ivohdkk!wBT4mWXIUjIh92btQBDJNXoPZqNTqxglXOivdCifXb8SPfidInz-OrqAe3rvJ-o%24"},{"_key":"dfe2c06db0e0","_type":"link","href":"https://urldefense.com/v3/__https:/nam11.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https*3A*2F*2Fwww.whitehouse.gov*2Fbriefing-room*2Fstatements-releases*2F2021*2F07*2F28*2Ffact-sheet-historic-bipartisan-infrastructure-deal*2F&data=04*7C01*7Cawest*40edf.org*7C00a61180cfe74bd4b7a008d96be8eb67*7Cfe4574edbcfd4bf0bde843713c3f434f*7C0*7C0*7C637659471469996635*7CUnknown*7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0*3D*7C1000&sdata=Ys2EjzdnqFEuHr2vvsE1sxmD7q4aGA0qIf2ct3ohous*3D&reserved=0__;JSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSU!!Ivohdkk!wBT4mWXIUjIh92btQBDJNXoPZqNTqxglXOivdCifXb8SPfidInz-OrqASNmgezA%24"}],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"9d3dacead46c","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"9d3dacead46c0","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"The bill doesn’t go far enough, says Mustafa Santiago Ali, who championed environmental justice at the Environmental Protection Agency for more than two decades, but “it’s a small step in the right direction.”"}],"markDefs":[],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"d8892f965460","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"d8892f9654600","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"He thinks infrastructure should mean more than the repair of roads and bridges and the production of new electric trucks to drive on them. It can lead to equity. Big organizations like Port Houston or the Texas Department of Transportation can take accountability for the history of injustice. They can rebuild the infrastructure of their relationships, which have tended to be “adversarial” and “extractive” of workers’ labor and people’s health, Ali says, especially in those communities that have been denied opportunity and protection through intentionally discriminatory policies like "},{"_key":"d8892f9654601","_type":"span","marks":["e5d30779c519"],"text":"redlining"},{"_key":"d8892f9654602","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":" and zoning, or a lack of it. We know all this now, he says. Infrastructure doesn’t have to force a false choice between the economy or the community, growth or death. Illegal air pollution in Texas, Indiana University researchers estimated, chokes at least "},{"_key":"d8892f9654603","_type":"span","marks":["941caac1cb51"],"text":"$240 million every year"},{"_key":"d8892f9654604","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":" out of the very same economy Port Houston prides itself on driving. “We shouldn’t put up this scenario of, ‘You either have to choose your life, or a job,’” Ali says. “What is it that communities want?”"}],"markDefs":[{"_key":"e5d30779c519","_type":"link","href":"https://www.houstonchronicle.com/local/gray-matters/article/Redlining-Houston-9970251.php"},{"_key":"941caac1cb51","_type":"link","href":"https://urldefense.com/v3/__https:/nam11.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https*3A*2F*2Fwww.texasobserver.org*2Fwhos-going-to-take-responsibility-for-air-pollution-in-texas*2F&data=04*7C01*7Cawest*40edf.org*7C00a61180cfe74bd4b7a008d96be8eb67*7Cfe4574edbcfd4bf0bde843713c3f434f*7C0*7C0*7C637659471469996635*7CUnknown*7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0*3D*7C1000&sdata=vSskKptbsaSnyv7ERgri5LOW32Xore08BJsl0*2F5DldY*3D&reserved=0__;JSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJQ!!Ivohdkk!wBT4mWXIUjIh92btQBDJNXoPZqNTqxglXOivdCifXb8SPfidInz-OrqA2Q7xgyU%24"}],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"6be12e1864c1","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"6be12e1864c10","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Cruz wants to stay home."}],"markDefs":[],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"ca2a72a84259","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"ca2a72a842590","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Carolyn Stone, who lives to the east of her in Channelview, wants to know what she’s breathing. And she wants to breathe clean air."}],"markDefs":[],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"394d00bd909f","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"394d00bd909f0","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"She lives near an “island” made of potentially toxic dredge spoils from previous infrastructure projects. She watched the dark plume from "},{"_key":"394d00bd909f1","_type":"span","marks":["f50b12e56a66"],"text":"the ITC disaster"},{"_key":"394d00bd909f2","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":" rise from her front door, the firefighting foam with "},{"_key":"394d00bd909f3","_type":"span","marks":["a2ca31f1fa8b"],"text":"forever chemicals"},{"_key":"394d00bd909f4","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":" swish down her street. More times than she can remember, she’s waited days for pollution control to come out to determine the cause of a worrying smell, only to tell her there’s nothing they can do. She grew up in Pasadena, and it’s always been like this, she says."}],"markDefs":[{"_key":"f50b12e56a66","_type":"link","href":"https://urldefense.com/v3/__https:/nam11.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https*3A*2F*2Fwww.houstonchronicle.com*2Fnews*2Fhouston-texas*2Fhouston*2Farticle*2FReport-ITC-did-not-have-emergency-shutoff-valve-14584762.php&data=04*7C01*7Cawest*40edf.org*7C00a61180cfe74bd4b7a008d96be8eb67*7Cfe4574edbcfd4bf0bde843713c3f434f*7C0*7C0*7C637659471470006590*7CUnknown*7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0*3D*7C1000&sdata=fTJqSqWr7cynHiCp80jL0lAPL7Li5XfoJypt31LkNwY*3D&reserved=0__;JSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSUl!!Ivohdkk!wBT4mWXIUjIh92btQBDJNXoPZqNTqxglXOivdCifXb8SPfidInz-OrqA4CoIats%24"},{"_key":"a2ca31f1fa8b","_type":"link","href":"https://urldefense.com/v3/__https:/nam11.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https*3A*2F*2Fwww.houstonchronicle.com*2Fnews*2Fhouston-texas*2Fhouston*2Farticle*2FEnvironmental-impacts-of-ITC-fire-to-be-presented-14806393.php&data=04*7C01*7Cawest*40edf.org*7C00a61180cfe74bd4b7a008d96be8eb67*7Cfe4574edbcfd4bf0bde843713c3f434f*7C0*7C0*7C637659471470006590*7CUnknown*7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0*3D*7C1000&sdata=tB*2FjvdknY*2BbAuRNk5h2MaDi8XNcE9dx5E83pyNFSRzg*3D&reserved=0__;JSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSU!!Ivohdkk!wBT4mWXIUjIh92btQBDJNXoPZqNTqxglXOivdCifXb8SPfidInz-OrqA-grLtqM%24"}],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"948cbabbe59c","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"948cbabbe59c0","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"She wants the port to put their money where their mouths are. If they can write blog posts calling themselves "},{"_key":"948cbabbe59c1","_type":"span","marks":["5498f351547a"],"text":"“environmental leaders,”"},{"_key":"948cbabbe59c2","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":" they can create a network of air monitors everyone can access. They can establish an alert system. They can invest in clean equipment. They can cut emissions. They can negotiate with the companies using their terminals to electrify their fleets. They can stop using communities as "},{"_key":"948cbabbe59c3","_type":"span","marks":["f13026a55ce9"],"text":"sacrifice zones"},{"_key":"948cbabbe59c4","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"."}],"markDefs":[{"_key":"5498f351547a","_type":"link","href":"https://urldefense.com/v3/__https:/nam11.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https*3A*2F*2Fporthouston.com*2Fenvironment*2Fland-management*2F&data=04*7C01*7Cawest*40edf.org*7C00a61180cfe74bd4b7a008d96be8eb67*7Cfe4574edbcfd4bf0bde843713c3f434f*7C0*7C0*7C637659471470016563*7CUnknown*7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0*3D*7C1000&sdata=2AuyyopVOpDm8Ozhd8OCyc*2FzvfVGRK84rP01nWvaMyY*3D&reserved=0__;JSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSU!!Ivohdkk!wBT4mWXIUjIh92btQBDJNXoPZqNTqxglXOivdCifXb8SPfidInz-OrqA59qHbqU%24"},{"_key":"f13026a55ce9","_type":"link","href":"https://urldefense.com/v3/__https:/nam11.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https*3A*2F*2Fgrist.org*2Ffix*2Famericans-live-sacrifice-zones-lets-fix-that*2F&data=04*7C01*7Cawest*40edf.org*7C00a61180cfe74bd4b7a008d96be8eb67*7Cfe4574edbcfd4bf0bde843713c3f434f*7C0*7C0*7C637659471470026518*7CUnknown*7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0*3D*7C1000&sdata=9uvV9208jms1gnfSUcx9mR7scmAC0X*2BzEmfuDoGJbfc*3D&reserved=0__;JSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSU!!Ivohdkk!wBT4mWXIUjIh92btQBDJNXoPZqNTqxglXOivdCifXb8SPfidInz-OrqAMmzDQ3I%24"}],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"7b60171d7665","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"7b60171d76650","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"And they can go after the money that will help them do it. The dredging project proves the port is perfectly willing to spend to make the Ship Channel safer and more accommodating for the largest ships. Are they willing to make the air safer for the smallest Houstonians, the "},{"_key":"7b60171d76651","_type":"span","marks":["ffd127acbc4b"],"text":"children within 2 miles who are 56 percent more likely to develop leukemia"},{"_key":"7b60171d76652","_type":"sp